<title type="html"><![CDATA[3/31(Thu) Will Aliens come to destroy the Earth? / How to spot false posts? (Host: Louie)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=603&amp;p=626#p626"><![CDATA[
Will Aliens come to destroy the Earth? / How to spot false posts? (Host: Louie)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40: Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />Session I:<br />Will Aliens come to destroy the Earth?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.space.com/29999-stephen-hawking-intelligent-alien-life-danger.html">https://www.space.com/29999-stephen-haw ... anger.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions<br /><br />1.Do you believe there are smarter, more advanced extraterrestrial being in the universe? Do you think it’s a good idea to discover them? Do you think it’s wise to keep on sending signals outwards to detect possible passers-by?<br />2.Someday, in case extraterrestrial aliens visited the Earth, do you tend to believe they come in peace to explore and do some study? Or they probably come to loot or to colonize?<br />3.There have been always many famous alien-related science fiction film, i.e. Close Encounters of the Third Kind (第三類接觸1977), ET(外星人1982), The X-Files (Drama, 1993), War of the Worlds(世界大戰Tom Cruise, 2005), ID4(星際終結者Will Smith, 1996). Which one of these or else do you prefer? Why?<br />4.Do you believe the Roswell UFO incident happened in Roswell, New Mexico, USA, 1947/7/4? In a storm night an UFO crashed to the ground and days after that a couple of “small man” were found dead inside a wreckage of a saucer-like object. Just 6 hours after the local press reported it on 7/9, the army said it’s but a meteorological balloon. What do you believe?<br /><br /><br />Session II:<br />How to spot false posts?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.indiatoday.in/fact-check/story/fact-check-old-image-ukrainian-children-sending-off-army-ukraine-russia-war-1918505-2022-02-27">https://www.indiatoday.in/fact-check/st ... 2022-02-27</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-trending-60654288">https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-trending-60654288</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions<br /><br />1.Have you ever received post on social media but proved to be false afterwards? What was it, for instance?<br />2.Why are there always people who like to fabricate news and to spread it over?<br />3.Would you normally believe those posts on social media and share it forward? Or would you doubt and verify (ex. google) it for reality?<br />4.Do you know Taiwan Fact Check Center (台灣事實查核中心)? Do you know <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tineye.com">https://tineye.com</a><!-- m -->? They help you verify a post is true or false. Will you check?<br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Sun Mar 27, 2022 9:50 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
